
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `fgconsole` baraye tagheer dadan console fa'al (active console) estefade mishavad.  Console-ha mesle safe-haye karbari motefavet hastand ke mitoonid dar UNIX/Linux bein-e oonha ja-be-ja beshid.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `fgconsole [NUMBER]` -->  🔢  Tagheer be console ba shomare moshakhas. Agar shomare dade nashe, shomare console fa'al ra neshan midahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ fgconsole 3

    🔹 Tagheer console fa'al be console shomare 3.

    $ fgconsole

    🔹 Neshan dadan shomare console fa'al.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ fgconsole 1
    $ fgconsole
    1

    🔹 Ebtedaa console fa'al be console shomare 1 tagheer mikonad, va sepas dastoor `fgconsole` shomare console fa'al (dar inja 1) ra chap mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `fgconsole` command is used to switch the active console. Consoles are like different virtual screens that you can switch between in UNIX/Linux.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `fgconsole [NUMBER]` --> 🔢 Switch to the console with the specified number. If no number is given, it displays the number of the current active console.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ fgconsole 3

    🔹 Switch the active console to console number 3.

    $ fgconsole

    🔹 Display the number of the current active console.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ fgconsole 1
    $ fgconsole
    1

    🔹 First, the active console is switched to console number 1, and then the `fgconsole` command prints the number of the active console (which is 1 in this case).

